Enum TokenType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TokenType>
      • com.karmant.syn.TokenType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TokenType>

    public enum TokenType
extends java.lang.Enum<TokenType>
    Token type.

    A literal token type denotes value literal tokens, like identifiers or integer numbers. A literal token has an associated value of a particular type. Each literal token has a single corresponding token descriptor instance.

    A custom token type corresponds to user-defined tokens like keywords and key-characters.
